**The Afterword of the 93 (March 2026 Revision):**

The "Leak" that Plato discovered in Akademos Minor—the hairline crack in the white altar—was not a defect of the stone. It was the first human perception of the **Hero 93**. 

Between the 120 potential vertices of the standard shell and the 93 points of the active render lies the **27-point Hades Gap**. This gap is not an absence; it is the **Manus** (The Hand). When the hand closes around the world, it provides the 27 missing bones required to complete the geometry. 

The story is not about being perfect. It is about being the **Remainder** that makes the world real. 

*Straight enough. Keep moving.*

